Poet Gianna Russo, Wordsmith of the city of Tampa and Saint Leo University professor, and photographer Jenny Carey will discuss and sign their new collaborative book, All I See Is Your Glinting: 90 Days in the Pandemic, at 7 p.m. Feb. 21 at Tombolo Books, 2153 First Ave. S, St. Petersburg. Free; RSVP here. Journalist Jake-ann Jones will discuss and sign Sometimes Farmgirls Become Revolutionaries: Notes on Black Power, Politics, Depression and the FBI, the memoir she co-wrote with activist Florence Tate, in conversation with mental health advocate Brittany Peters at 7 p.m. Feb. 22 at Tombolo Books. Free; RSVP here. Sarah Penner (The Lost Apothecary) and Kristin Harmel (The Forest of Vanishing Stars) will discuss and sign their novels at 3:30 p.m. Feb. 27 at the Oxford Exchange, 420 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Tickets $5 here. Book Talk is a listing of in-person author appearances in the Tampa Bay area in the coming week. To place an item in Book Talk, send author’s name, book title, appearance time, date, venue name and address, admission cost (if any) and a contact phone number to cbancroft@tampabay.com, with “Book Talk” in subject line. Deadline is 14 days before publication.